This paper is primarily focused on deep learning models, specifically generative adversarial models (GANs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the robustness of GANs in the context of computer vision (cs.CV) and adversarial attacks (cs.CR). The paper also explores theoretical conditions for robustness, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes variations of GANs that are more robust, which falls under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
